description: Climb up tallest part of boulder to top out for a beautiful view.
Low Crux, poor rock quality, but great landing zone (one pad and spotter) and beautiful view. If you happen to be in the area and want a hike, climb, and a good view check it out!
Big heel hook press mantel up the center wall to beautiful strong crimps. Top out and enjoy the view.
location: Right of Black Panther and left of Dare Devil. Obvious mantle ledge.

description: Start on slightly less than vertical rock and work up through pockets and rails to the beautiful finish.  Enjoy the view.
location: This route is located on the left end of the wall that share's Glenn's Route and the Crack Route.  It climbs the arete.

description: #9 in Sven's; named for the beautiful view. Climb just left of corner on nice ledges. A good warm-up for the area.
location: Back right corner of Overhang Tower (Blockhead).
protection: 20-30ft slings for TR. Pro looks sparse but doable.

description: sit start into slope-y underclings, beautiful views.
location: Park at intersection of paseo del mar and via berri at the cliffs, hike down and follow rocky beach to the left. The climbs are at the little basalt vista.
protection: bring a pad and maybe a buddy

description: Fun, positive climbing on beautiful rock until a thin crux at the 5th bolt. Slightly tenuous moves take you to the chains and a beautiful view.  Well worth the scramble up to the start.  WARNING! After the 9th bolt, a loose block/flake must be avoided by going up and left.
location: Climb an easy 4th class gully up to the left of Nice Jugs. Be wary of loose rock near the top.

description: Closed project please do not climb.. . Climbs through the roof on the right side through the seam weaknesses. Beautiful enjoyable climbing above the roof to the top of the cliff-line. Great view!
location: Left of "Froop there is is" under the giant Pinnacle roof

fa: Scott Duemler, Aaron Collins, Bob Petit
description: Very aesthetic line above pool on slab left of long arÃªte. Easy climbing, beautiful views. Have a party!
location: Starts just above water at pool on right side of wall.

description: Bolted on lead in a hail storm, some of the clipping stances are awkward down low, but once through the third bolt the climbing moves right and eases up to enjoyable movements and a beautiful view from the top.
